#  COVID-19 Data Analysis Project

## Overview
This project analyzes COVID-19 data using Python to understand trends in:
- Daily confirmed cases
- Daily deaths
- Recovery patterns

The goal is to practice data loading, cleaning, and visualization using real-world time-series data.

---

##  Tools & Technologies
- Python
- Pandas
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn

---

##  Dataset
Source: Kaggle (Our World in Data / Johns Hopkins COVID Dataset)

Dataset includes:
- Date
- Location (Country)
- New Cases
- New Deaths
- Total Recoveries

---

## Implementation Steps
1. Loaded dataset using Pandas.
2. Converted date column to datetime format.
3. Filtered data for a specific country (e.g., India).
4. Handled missing values.
5. Sorted data by date.
6. Created line plots for trend analysis.

---

 **Key Insights
- Identified major COVID waves through spikes in daily cases.
- Observed correlation between case peaks and death rates.
- Recovery trend showed steady improvement post peak periods.

---

## Output
- Line chart of daily cases
- Line chart of daily deaths
- Line chart of recovery trend

---

##  Learning Outcome
- Time-series data handling
- Data cleaning techniques
- Visual storytelling using graphs

---

##  Future Improvements
- Add 7-day rolling average smoothing
- Compare multiple countries
- Interactive dashboard using Plotly
